the people who are--

00:17:20.339 --> 00:17:25.470
he made the people who are
verifying the transactions,

00:17:25.470 --> 00:17:26.849
they have to apply
the processing

00:17:26.849 --> 00:17:30.030
power of their computers in
order to confirm and verify

00:17:30.030 --> 00:17:31.014
those transactions.

00:17:31.014 --> 00:17:32.430
And in return for
doing that, they

00:17:32.430 --> 00:17:34.200
are then rewarded
with new bitcoins.

00:17:34.200 --> 00:17:38.044
So it's kind of a clearinghouse
and a central mint all in one.

00:17:38.044 --> 00:17:39.210
But it's not a central mint.

00:17:39.210 --> 00:17:40.340
It's decentralized.

